## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

This document covers the Kotlin/JVM implementation of the Graph Engine — the second batch (K2) of the Code Intelligence v2 Feature Parity Sync. This includes:

* Call graph construction from parsed ASTs (function/method call relationships)
* Dependency graph construction (module/file import relationships)
* Impact analysis (determine which code is affected by a change)
* Graph traversal algorithms (BFS, DFS, shortest path)
* Cycle detection (circular dependencies, recursive call chains)
* Graph serialization and querying via MCP tools

The Graph Engine consumes AST and symbol data from KSA-172 (Tree-sitter Core + Parsers) and provides graph-based analysis to downstream features (AI Context KSA-174, Code Quality KSA-175, Security Analysis KSA-176).

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* Tree-sitter parsing and AST construction (KSA-172)
* AI context tools and token budget management (KSA-174)
* Code quality metrics (cyclomatic complexity, cognitive complexity) (KSA-175)
* Security analysis (taint analysis, CFG/DFG) (KSA-176)
* Similarity detection and embeddings (KSA-177)
* Python track implementation (KSA-179)
* UI/frontend components (KSA-170)
* Changes to the nodejs reference implementation (KSA-144)
* Database persistence of graph data (future enhancement)

