## 5. Risks and Assumptions

### 5.1 Risks

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Risk | Impact | Likelihood | Mitigation |
| Call resolution inaccuracy for dynamic languages | Medium | High | Over-approximate: include all possible targets; mark confidence level |
| Memory pressure from large graphs (10K+ nodes) | High | Medium | Lazy edge loading; graph partitioning by module; off-heap storage |
| Performance degradation on monorepo-scale projects | High | Medium | Incremental updates; parallel graph construction; caching |
| Divergence from nodejs reference due to resolution differences | Medium | Medium | Strict test fixtures; automated CI comparison |
| Cycle detection performance on dense graphs | Medium | Low | Tarjan’s algorithm (linear time); early termination for known patterns |
| Import resolution failures for complex module systems | Medium | High | Fallback to unresolved edges; configurable resolution strategies |

### 5.2 Assumptions

* KSA-172 provides complete symbol tables with scope information
* KSA-172 provides import/export statement extraction
* KSA-144 Batch 2 nodejs implementation is the single source of truth for graph structure
* Graph data is held in-memory (no persistent storage required for v1)
* Custom adjacency list data structures (no external graph library dependency)
* Kotlin coroutines available for parallel graph construction
* JDK 17+ is the minimum supported runtime

