## 8. Appendix

### Glossary

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Term | Definition |
| Call Graph | Directed graph where nodes are functions and edges represent call relationships |
| Dependency Graph | Directed graph where nodes are files/modules and edges represent import relationships |
| Impact Analysis | Determining which code is affected by a change to a specific symbol or file |
| BFS | Breadth-First Search — graph traversal visiting neighbors before going deeper |
| DFS | Depth-First Search — graph traversal visiting depth before breadth |
| Cycle | A path in a directed graph that starts and ends at the same node |
| In-degree | Number of incoming edges to a node (number of callers) |
| Betweenness Centrality | Measure of how often a node appears on shortest paths between other nodes |
| Hot Path | A function/method that is called frequently or sits on many critical paths |
| Transitive Closure | All nodes reachable from a starting node through any number of edges |
| MCP | Model Context Protocol — interface for AI tool integration |

